parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of critical vehicle functions, such as headlights, brake lights, and power windows, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The car loses all electric power
including headlights
brake lights
and power windows
while the engine continues to run.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and parking brake systems can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the parking brake engages unexpectedly
and the vehicle loses motive power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blind spot indicator can cause the driver to be unaware of vehicles in their blind spot, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The blind spot indicator does not warn of vehicles in the blind spot.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the automatic start/stop feature can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's engine shuts off unexpectedly
and the vehicle will not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sunroof leak can cause water damage and electrical failures, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the sunroof
causing damage to the interior and electrical systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can prevent the driver from warning pedestrians or other vehicles in emergency situations, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The horn does not work or works intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear window defroster can cause the rear window to crack or shatter, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear window defroster overheats
causing the window to crack or shatter.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed acceleration from a standing start can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially when merging into traffic or navigating intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or delays accelerating from a standstill
often taking 2-6 seconds to respond to the accelerator pedal. The engine may remain at idle
and the vehicle may not shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The panoramic sunroof leaks can cause water damage, mold, and electrical issues, while the explosions can lead to shattered glass, injuries, and accidents.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the panoramic sunroof
often causing mold and water damage. In some cases
the sunroof may shatter or explode without warning
causing a loud noise and potentially injuring occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to properly repair the TPMS software recall can lead to incorrect tire pressure readings, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle's TPMS system may not function correctly
providing inaccurate tire pressure readings or failing to alert the driver to low tire pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty door switch can cause electrical issues, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The door switch may malfunction
causing random warnings or errors on the dashboard display.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The KESSI key fob connectivity issues can cause inconvenience, stranding, or accidents, especially in cold weather.
symptoms: The KESSI key fob may lose power or connectivity in cold weather
preventing the vehicle from unlocking or starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The autonomous emergency braking system malfunctions can cause accidents or injuries, especially if the system engages unnecessarily.
symptoms: The autonomous emergency braking system may engage unnecessarily
causing the vehicle to come to an abrupt stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Car-Net connectivity issues can cause inconvenience, stranding, or accidents, especially if the system fails to provide critical information.
symptoms: The Car-Net system may not function correctly
preventing the driver from accessing important features or services.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wind Vibration Noise and Air Pressure Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The wind vibration noise and air pressure issues can cause physical discomfort, distraction, or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience wind vibration noise or air pressure issues when windows are rolled down
causing discomfort or distraction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and clutch issues can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to accelerate, leading to safety concerns, especially when merging into traffic or driving on busy roads.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the transmission shudders or vibrates
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system leaks and failures can cause fuel to leak onto the hot engine, leading to a risk of fire or explosion.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the engine
the vehicle goes into "Limp Home" mode
the Check Engine and EPC lights come on
a warning message displays on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Software and electronic issues can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to safety concerns, especially when driving on busy roads.
symptoms: The vehicle's warning systems malfunction
the vehicle's systems fail to function properly
the vehicle's software bugs cause issues with the airbag deployment system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system issues can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to safety concerns, especially when driving on busy roads.
symptoms: The brake system malfunctions
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle's brake power boost fails.
